I"0<p><strong>Type casting is the conversion from one dataype to another.</strong> PHP also allow type casting. We can convert from various datatypes e.g int to float or int to string e.t.c. Here i’ve solved various examples in which i’m switching between multiple dataypes,</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;?php
$a=true;
$a=(string) $a;

$b="300";
$b=(int) $b;

$c=1;
$c= (float) $c;

$d="abc";
$d=(boolean) $d;

$e=10;
$e=(array) $e;

$f=20;
$f=(object) $f;

// $x=["30"];
// $x=(string) $x;
// var_dump($x);
?&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Also, keep in mind array to string conversion is directly not allowed in php. You’ll get an error like this,</p>

